1
00:01:29,550 --> 00:01:34,930
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:37,800
[Episode 19]

3
00:01:44,310 --> 00:01:45,070
Sen.

4
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,950
Sen, look who's here.

5
00:01:50,960 --> 00:01:51,800
Sen.

6
00:01:52,110 --> 00:01:52,960
Zhuang Cent!

7
00:01:53,490 --> 00:01:54,160
Who?

8
00:01:57,310 --> 00:01:58,600
Oh my god, Xiaodan!

9
00:01:59,890 --> 00:02:00,420
Oh my god.

10
00:02:03,150 --> 00:02:03,680
Oh my god.

11
00:02:05,510 --> 00:02:06,240
You're back?

12
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:07,280
Yeah.

13
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:08,030
Lei!

14
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:09,870
-Gosh!
-You were quite fast.

15
00:02:09,870 --> 00:02:11,930
I heard you shouting from miles away.

16
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:13,150
Sen.

17
00:02:13,150 --> 00:02:15,880
-You never hear people calling your name.
-Look.

18
00:02:16,430 --> 00:02:18,150
This area used to be deserted.

19
00:02:18,150 --> 00:02:18,910
It was only after

20
00:02:18,910 --> 00:02:20,170
we set up our stall that

21
00:02:20,470 --> 00:02:21,680
that so many vendors gradually moved in.

22
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:22,750
Isn't that the roller rink?

23
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:24,590
Yeah. It's a dance hall now.

24
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:25,590
A dance hall now?

25
00:02:25,590 --> 00:02:26,750
They do roller skating in the afternoon.

26
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:27,360
You see?

27
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:28,190
With all these lights

28
00:02:28,190 --> 00:02:29,190
and the canopy,

29
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:30,240
-it looks like this now.
-Xiaodan, Xia Lei?

30
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,190
It's really nice.

31
00:02:31,190 --> 00:02:31,680
Dongdong?

32
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:32,660
-Dongdong.
-When did you come back?

33
00:02:32,660 --> 00:02:33,710
Just got back.

34
00:02:33,829 --> 00:02:35,090
Why didn't you tell us?

35
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:36,680
Which table is empty?

36
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:37,520
That table, that one.

37
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,120
-Okay.
-Over there.

38
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:38,750
Let's go. This way.

39
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:39,560
Why didn't you tell us?

40
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:40,310
Did you miss me?

41
00:02:40,310 --> 00:02:40,680
I did.

42
00:02:40,750 --> 00:02:41,960
How is it? Not bad, right?

43
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:42,870
It's really nice.

44
00:02:42,870 --> 00:02:43,870
What do you want to eat?

45
00:02:43,870 --> 00:02:44,800
Anything is fine.

46
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:45,430
I'll go get...

47
00:02:45,430 --> 00:02:47,000
Dongdong, get a fruit platter

48
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:47,930
and some snacks.

49
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:48,400
Okay.

50
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:50,680
This is great.

51
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,960
The roller rink
was combined with a dance hall.

52
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:54,910
It's a roller rink in the afternoon.

53
00:02:54,910 --> 00:02:55,630
Once it gets dark

54
00:02:55,630 --> 00:02:58,280
and the lights come on, it turns into a dance hall.

55
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:00,000
I've never even been to a dance hall in Shanghai.

56
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,000
So well-behaved?

57
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:02,310
Of course.

58
00:03:02,870 --> 00:03:03,730
What about you?

59
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,360
I went to the Paramount once.

60
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:05,910
Xiaodan!

61
00:03:05,910 --> 00:03:06,840
Nana.

62
00:03:07,150 --> 00:03:07,680
Xia Lei.

63
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:08,940
Nana, long time no see.

64
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:09,840
Let me get that for you.

65
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:10,340
Da.

66
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,120
Da.

67
00:03:11,310 --> 00:03:12,400
Did you get taller?

68
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:13,590
Da, Da.

69
00:03:13,590 --> 00:03:14,990
It's been years.

70
00:03:15,430 --> 00:03:16,960
This place was set up by me, Da,

71
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:18,760
and Zhigang. We did it together.

72
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,150
-Please take a seat.
-You go ahead.

73
00:03:21,150 --> 00:03:23,950
You... you're the guy who pushed me into the water.

74
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:26,040
You borrowed my school uniform.

75
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:26,640
Chunchun.

76
00:03:27,870 --> 00:03:28,910
You two are colleagues now?

77
00:03:28,910 --> 00:03:29,560
What a coincidence.

78
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:30,470
Colleagues?

79
00:03:30,470 --> 00:03:31,710
Just getting by.

80
00:03:32,590 --> 00:03:33,960
Are you two college students?

81
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:34,430
Yes.

82
00:03:34,430 --> 00:03:35,240
Impressive.

83
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:35,800
Studying in Shanghai.

84
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,750
Come on, let's drink.

85
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:37,310
It's on me.

86
00:03:37,310 --> 00:03:38,000
Come on.

87
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:38,750
Da is here.

88
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:40,410
You think you need to treat us?

89
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,120
It's on Da.

90
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:42,710
Drink as much as you want.

91
00:03:42,710 --> 00:03:43,870
-Okay.
-Dance if you want.

92
00:03:43,870 --> 00:03:44,710
-Alright.
-Thanks, Da.

93
00:03:44,710 --> 00:03:45,430
You guys chat.

94
00:03:45,430 --> 00:03:46,240
Okay. Okay.

95
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:47,540
Take good care of them.

96
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,150
Come on, have another drink.

97
00:03:51,150 --> 00:03:51,710
Cheers to happiness.

98
00:03:51,710 --> 00:03:52,520
-Come on.
-Cheers.

99
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,150
Come on.

100
00:03:53,910 --> 00:03:54,430
Cheers.

101
00:03:58,910 --> 00:03:59,560
Slow down.

102
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,830
Why are you drinking so fast?

103
00:04:00,830 --> 00:04:01,350
Gosh.

104
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:02,120
So fast?

105
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:02,840
You finished yours?

106
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:04,360
-Give me another one.
-Open some more bottles.

107
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,560
What are you doing?

108
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:06,360
I'm happy.

109
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,030
Here, here, here.

110
00:04:07,030 --> 00:04:07,910
We haven't seen
each other for a long time.

111
00:04:07,910 --> 00:04:08,510
Thank you.

112
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,380
How long will you stay?

113
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,590
Just the National Day holiday.

114
00:04:11,590 --> 00:04:12,400
Nice.

115
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,400
Is Shanghai fun?

116
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:15,210
It's just so-so.

117
00:04:15,460 --> 00:04:16,860
Come on. Let's talk.

118
00:04:18,110 --> 00:04:20,370
Come on. Let me see what's wrong with you.

119
00:04:28,390 --> 00:04:29,190
What's wrong?

120
00:04:31,630 --> 00:04:32,390
What happened?

121
00:04:32,390 --> 00:04:34,630
Not happy in Shanghai?

122
00:04:35,190 --> 00:04:36,360
My internship is over.

123
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:37,670
The company didn't keep me.

124
00:04:37,670 --> 00:04:39,630
I thought it was something serious.

125
00:04:39,630 --> 00:04:40,630
If this one doesn't want you,

126
00:04:40,630 --> 00:04:41,890
just find another one.

127
00:04:41,909 --> 00:04:43,570
What? You can't find another?

128
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:46,440
How should I explain this? It's just...

129
00:04:46,850 --> 00:04:48,240
If this internship period passes,

130
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,750
all the good jobs will be taken,

131
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:51,610
and I'll only have the leftovers.

132
00:04:52,310 --> 00:04:54,040
You worry too much.

133
00:04:54,870 --> 00:04:57,430
Who cares if it's a good job or a bad job?

134
00:04:57,430 --> 00:04:58,830
You made it out of our small town

135
00:04:58,830 --> 00:05:00,190
and got to Shanghai.

136
00:05:00,510 --> 00:05:02,430
Staying there is what matters most.

137
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:03,070
Right?

138
00:05:03,510 --> 00:05:04,630
It's fine. Really.

139
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:07,850
What did your parents say this time you came back?

140
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:10,680
Don't mention it.

141
00:05:10,870 --> 00:05:13,400
I dreaded calling them when I was in Shanghai.

142
00:05:13,830 --> 00:05:14,920
Whenever we talk about work

143
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:15,720
or internships,

144
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:17,630
it's always the same three phrases:

145
00:05:17,630 --> 00:05:18,950
"Work hard,"

146
00:05:19,430 --> 00:05:20,830
"be humble and prudent,"

147
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:22,680
and "success will follow naturally."

148
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:24,430
I get anxious just hearing it.

149
00:05:24,430 --> 00:05:25,070
I tell them,

150
00:05:25,070 --> 00:05:27,040
"Mom, Dad, times have changed.

151
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,750
It's not like back in your day.

152
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:31,390
Smart people have already overtaken you.

153
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:32,360
Success will follow naturally?

154
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:32,950
By the time that happens...

155
00:05:32,950 --> 00:05:33,920
I won't...

156
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:36,070
I won't be able to enjoy the success."

157
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:37,409
Come on.

158
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,480
About this...

159
00:05:41,430 --> 00:05:44,040
Your folks are just worried about you.

160
00:05:44,190 --> 00:05:45,360
Right? They worry,

161
00:05:45,430 --> 00:05:46,600
but they can't help.

162
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:48,670
Besides, they're not wrong.

163
00:05:48,930 --> 00:05:50,930
Right? You should work hard.

164
00:05:51,970 --> 00:05:53,350
Don't get so worked up every day.

165
00:05:53,350 --> 00:05:54,610
Why get worked up over your own family?

166
00:05:54,610 --> 00:05:56,510
-Working hard...
-Let me tell you.

167
00:05:56,510 --> 00:05:58,720
You're lucky to have someone nagging you.

168
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:00,430
Look at me, nobody nags me.

169
00:06:02,270 --> 00:06:03,670
Doesn't Xiaodan nag you?

170
00:06:03,950 --> 00:06:05,680
We just communicate.

171
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:07,900
It's different from talking to family.

172
00:06:10,910 --> 00:06:12,100
But, you know,

173
00:06:12,190 --> 00:06:13,720
you two have been together for so long—

174
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:14,600
almost three years now, right?

175
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,860
Well... what's your plan for the future?

176
00:06:18,830 --> 00:06:20,600
I'll save some money first.

177
00:06:23,190 --> 00:06:24,830
Then I'll go to Shanghai too.

178
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,250
To be closer to you guys.

179
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:28,020
I'll find a livelihood there.

180
00:06:28,070 --> 00:06:29,730
Maybe start a small business.

181
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,750
Anyway, if I keep working here,

182
00:06:31,750 --> 00:06:32,680
what do you think

183
00:06:33,750 --> 00:06:34,870
I can do?

184
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:36,800
Go back to the plant to be a welder?

185
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:39,440
Chief Engineer Yan wouldn't agree to that, right?

186
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:41,100
I have to make money to get out.

187
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,630
Don't just tell me that.

188
00:06:42,630 --> 00:06:43,950
You should tell her.

189
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:45,810
You two need to communicate more.

190
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:47,870
I just started everything.

191
00:06:47,870 --> 00:06:49,120
What can I tell her?

192
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:50,159
There's nothing to talk about.

193
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:52,190
Wouldn't that be just making empty promises?

194
00:06:52,190 --> 00:06:53,070
I can't do that.

195
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,630
She won't be here much longer anyway.

196
00:06:55,630 --> 00:06:56,720
She's going back to Shanghai soon.

197
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,630
I know, I know.

198
00:06:57,630 --> 00:06:59,070
You need to talk to her

199
00:06:59,830 --> 00:07:01,690
to see what your future plans are.

200
00:07:01,950 --> 00:07:03,610
You need to listen to her more.

201
00:07:04,390 --> 00:07:05,000
Chunchun.

202
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:06,630
I think...

203
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:10,980
you've met more people
and experienced more things

204
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:12,600
than I have.

205
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:14,680
So you must know more than me.

206
00:07:14,990 --> 00:07:16,520
I have something to ask you.

207
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:17,800
I want your opinion.

208
00:07:18,260 --> 00:07:19,120
Sure, go ahead.

209
00:07:19,130 --> 00:07:19,730
What is it?

210
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:24,720
I have a friend.

211
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:28,410
She's been in a long-distance relationship
for 3 years.

212
00:07:29,250 --> 00:07:30,770
And she...

213
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,830
now has a chance to study abroad.

214
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:37,180
She's always wanted to go abroad.

215
00:07:38,159 --> 00:07:41,220
But she and her boyfriend have had a good relationship.

216
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:43,830
She's very confused.

217
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:48,510
She doesn't know what to choose.

218
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:53,260
I don't know much about studying abroad.

219
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:54,480
But I think

220
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:56,159
your friend wants her boyfriend

221
00:07:56,159 --> 00:07:57,760
to make the decision for her.

222
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,480
Come on. Let's have a drink.

223
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,510
-Easy.
-Are you okay?

224
00:08:03,510 --> 00:08:04,390
You can't even walk straight.

225
00:08:04,390 --> 00:08:06,190
No problem. Come on. I'm happy.

226
00:08:06,190 --> 00:08:07,720
It's good to see you guys.

227
00:08:08,110 --> 00:08:10,110
I met some new friends from the past.

228
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:12,190
I forgot my bag.

229
00:08:12,190 --> 00:08:14,120
I'll go back to the dance hall to get it.

230
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,630
Otherwise, you'll have to wait for me later.

231
00:08:15,630 --> 00:08:16,090
Come on!

232
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:18,950
Boss Si, I... I'm really grateful to you.

233
00:08:19,630 --> 00:08:21,090
But this "cough syrup"...

234
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,240
We really can't sell it anymore.

235
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,800
Da has found out.

236
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:24,710
So...

237
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,690
I asked you here today to see

238
00:08:27,010 --> 00:08:28,570
if there's any other way.

239
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,080
Any other way?

240
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:33,049
There is one.

241
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:40,200
Take this...

242
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:41,789
Let me.

243
00:08:43,870 --> 00:08:44,720
Hide it well.

244
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:47,080
Boss Si, what do you mean?

245
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,440
What do you mean?

246
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:50,790
Didn't you ask me to find a solution for you?

247
00:08:50,790 --> 00:08:53,150
I admit Da and I have different philosophies.

248
00:08:53,150 --> 00:08:54,330
But Da is my brother.

249
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:55,840
I can't do this.

250
00:08:56,190 --> 00:08:57,390
Now you're brothers?

251
00:08:58,270 --> 00:08:59,510
Now you are not following me around,

252
00:08:59,510 --> 00:09:00,840
begging me for a chance?

253
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,130
Zhigang, you...

254
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:03,630
You don't need to worry.

255
00:09:03,630 --> 00:09:05,200
For this amount of ecstasy,

256
00:09:05,550 --> 00:09:07,750
Da would only be sentenced to 5 years.

257
00:09:08,110 --> 00:09:08,750
Right?

258
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:11,360
While he's in jail, you can make more money.

259
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,320
Right? When he gets out,

260
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:13,550
if you feel guilty,

261
00:09:13,550 --> 00:09:15,030
you can compensate him more.

262
00:09:15,030 --> 00:09:16,160
Wouldn't that work?

263
00:09:20,550 --> 00:09:22,790
Are you alright? Can you handle your liquor?

264
00:09:22,790 --> 00:09:23,960
You won't throw up, will you?

265
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:25,800
What's wrong? Why are you running?

266
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:26,790
Something happened.

267
00:09:26,790 --> 00:09:27,240
What?

268
00:09:27,510 --> 00:09:29,870
I was just in the dance hall office,

269
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:33,470
and I heard Zhigang and Wei Si plotting against Da.

270
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:34,240
Plotting against Da?

271
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,370
He told him to plant drugs at his place.

272
00:09:36,510 --> 00:09:38,230
Are they still there?

273
00:09:38,270 --> 00:09:40,200
They're inside. I just heard them.

274
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:40,870
It's okay.

275
00:09:40,870 --> 00:09:41,670
Stay out of it.

276
00:09:42,590 --> 00:09:44,680
Don't tell anyone about this.

277
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:46,630
Just pretend you don't know.

278
00:09:46,630 --> 00:09:47,490
I'll handle it.

279
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:48,870
Take Xiaodan home.

280
00:09:48,870 --> 00:09:50,120
Xiaodan, go with Xia Lei.

281
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:50,720
Where are you going?

282
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,150
You don't have to get involved.

283
00:09:52,150 --> 00:09:53,810
If I don't step in, no one will.

284
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,530
I didn't know there were

285
00:10:07,550 --> 00:10:09,480
so many problems in the dance hall.

286
00:10:09,790 --> 00:10:10,750
And drugs?

287
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,360
He is calm today.

288
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,720
What about the future?

289
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:14,440
What about tomorrow, or the day after?

290
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:16,040
If something worse happens,

291
00:10:16,270 --> 00:10:17,750
will he still be able to keep his cool?

292
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:19,440
What if he really acts on impulse?

293
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:20,670
There's trouble every single day.

294
00:10:20,670 --> 00:10:21,360
Alright, alright.

295
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:23,550
You're exaggerating too much.

296
00:10:24,430 --> 00:10:25,070
Did...

297
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:27,670
Did you tell him about going abroad?

298
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,970
I was about to tell him tonight.

299
00:10:34,390 --> 00:10:35,550
But...

300
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,900
we were eating and having fun,

301
00:10:38,630 --> 00:10:40,910
and then he had
to deal with the dance hall business

302
00:10:40,910 --> 00:10:41,970
and left suddenly.

303
00:10:42,270 --> 00:10:43,400
How could I tell him?

304
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:45,200
You didn't tell him,

305
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:47,000
so how would he know?

306
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:47,670
Right?

307
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:48,960
You...

308
00:10:50,030 --> 00:10:53,150
Look, you two need to communicate about this.

309
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:56,960
Why is he making money at the dance hall?

310
00:10:57,390 --> 00:10:58,850
Isn't it for the two of you?

311
00:10:58,870 --> 00:10:59,510
Right?

312
00:11:00,150 --> 00:11:01,150
You have to learn to communicate.

313
00:11:01,150 --> 00:11:03,210
Just thinking about it isn't enough.

314
00:11:03,390 --> 00:11:04,200
Is it?

315
00:11:04,650 --> 00:11:05,600
Think about it.

316
00:11:49,870 --> 00:11:50,930
But the reality is,

317
00:11:51,270 --> 00:11:53,030
he is at the East Chemical Plant,

318
00:11:53,030 --> 00:11:54,360
and you are in Shanghai.

319
00:11:54,550 --> 00:11:56,080
If you two want to meet,

320
00:11:56,550 --> 00:11:58,550
you can still do it with some effort.

321
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:00,790
But once you go abroad,

322
00:12:01,310 --> 00:12:03,220
you really will be worlds apart.

323
00:12:05,390 --> 00:12:06,650
We have agreed on this—

324
00:12:06,870 --> 00:12:07,870
after I graduate from college,

325
00:12:07,870 --> 00:12:09,600
we will move forward together.

326
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:12,160
Then you should be more confident.

327
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:14,000
You should stride forward

328
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,440
without hesitation

329
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,580
and see if he can catch up with you.

330
00:12:17,630 --> 00:12:18,830
This is your destiny.

331
00:12:19,670 --> 00:12:22,550
Magellan was destined to sail around the world.

332
00:12:32,630 --> 00:12:35,430
Help me move this table. I want to put it over there.

333
00:12:48,810 --> 00:12:50,670
Do you know what I just thought of?

334
00:12:51,510 --> 00:12:52,600
Remember back in elementary school,

335
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,130
when we were moving tables?

336
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:57,220
Why did we move them back then?

337
00:13:01,390 --> 00:13:02,200
Because

338
00:13:03,390 --> 00:13:04,600
our grades were bad.

339
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:08,640
We really wanted the teacher's praise.

340
00:13:11,190 --> 00:13:12,190
We were naive.

341
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:15,200
If I had another chance,

342
00:13:15,870 --> 00:13:18,530
I think I could actually pay attention in class.

343
00:13:29,790 --> 00:13:31,120
Why are the police here?

344
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:35,650
Do you know what's going on?

345
00:13:38,910 --> 00:13:39,670
I don't know.

346
00:13:41,940 --> 00:13:43,400
Officer, what's going on?

347
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:46,290
-What happened?
-I don't know.

348
00:13:49,910 --> 00:13:50,790
What's wrong, Captain Feng?

349
00:13:50,790 --> 00:13:51,790
A surprise check.

350
00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:53,790
Someone reported

351
00:13:54,870 --> 00:13:57,000
that your dance hall is selling drugs.

352
00:13:57,630 --> 00:13:58,890
Get everyone out here.

353
00:14:02,790 --> 00:14:03,990
Everyone, come down!

354
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:09,200
Xiaodan, why are you here?

355
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:15,510
Stand properly over there.

356
00:14:15,510 --> 00:14:16,370
Stand in a line.

357
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:18,910
Search.

358
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:39,720
Xiaodan, go!

359
00:14:40,860 --> 00:14:41,620
Hurry!

360
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:47,330
Captain, I found it.

361
00:14:48,620 --> 00:14:49,310
What?

362
00:14:50,600 --> 00:14:51,200
What is it?

363
00:15:13,790 --> 00:15:14,650
What are these?

364
00:15:16,280 --> 00:15:17,080
Milk tablets.

365
00:15:18,150 --> 00:15:20,550
You keep a bag of milk tablets in the office?

366
00:15:20,630 --> 00:15:21,110
Yeah.

367
00:15:21,790 --> 00:15:23,040
Are you messing with the police?

368
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:24,370
Well, I love milk tablets.

369
00:15:24,370 --> 00:15:25,370
Is that illegal?

370
00:15:26,720 --> 00:15:28,050
Listen to me, all of you.

371
00:15:28,550 --> 00:15:30,580
Filing a false police report is illegal.

372
00:15:30,580 --> 00:15:32,580
You would face legal consequences.

373
00:15:32,870 --> 00:15:33,440
Yes, sir.

374
00:15:34,520 --> 00:15:35,100
Let's go.

375
00:15:38,390 --> 00:15:38,920
Make way.

376
00:15:42,180 --> 00:15:42,840
Make way, everyone!

377
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:44,550
-What happened?
-Captain Feng, can you tell us

378
00:15:44,550 --> 00:15:45,480
what happened?

379
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:49,030
Xiaoman!

380
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:57,030
They're all gone.

381
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:57,940
Should we go in?

382
00:15:59,340 --> 00:16:01,340
You go ahead. I need to clear my head.

383
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:12,360
Xiaoman! Xiaoman!

384
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:17,740
Xiaoman! Xiaoman! Xiaoman!

385
00:16:18,670 --> 00:16:20,200
Xiaoman!

386
00:16:37,550 --> 00:16:38,810
What's wrong with you?

387
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:41,050
Why don't you go inside?

388
00:16:41,790 --> 00:16:43,000
Why would I go in?

389
00:16:43,130 --> 00:16:45,060
What did I tell you yesterday? See?

390
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,640
The police came today.

391
00:16:49,910 --> 00:16:51,710
I'm afraid it'll be like before.

392
00:16:52,630 --> 00:16:54,630
I'm afraid to see that again.

393
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:55,600
I'm telling you,

394
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,460
this must be a misunderstanding.

395
00:16:57,630 --> 00:16:59,240
Right? Didn't the police say

396
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:00,440
it was a false report?

397
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:02,630
Besides, Xiaoman is focusing on his career now.

398
00:17:02,630 --> 00:17:04,890
He wouldn't do anything messy like that.

399
00:17:08,930 --> 00:17:11,589
Da, since when are you addicted to milk tablets?

400
00:17:14,460 --> 00:17:15,920
Why don't you ask Zhigang?

401
00:17:20,349 --> 00:17:21,150
Why?

402
00:17:24,690 --> 00:17:26,750
Why did you conspire with an outsider

403
00:17:28,339 --> 00:17:29,690
to frame me?

404
00:17:31,590 --> 00:17:32,790
You're asking me why?

405
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:34,330
Wang Tieda.

406
00:17:36,070 --> 00:17:38,470
I've treated you as a brother my whole life.

407
00:17:39,350 --> 00:17:40,400
What do you treat me as?

408
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:41,310
Your servant?

409
00:17:41,790 --> 00:17:43,110
We're 30!

410
00:17:43,870 --> 00:17:45,020
We have no money

411
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:46,410
and no jobs.

412
00:17:47,150 --> 00:17:49,160
Now there's a chance to make good money,

413
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:51,160
but you guys think it's dirty money.

414
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:54,510
Growing up,

415
00:17:54,510 --> 00:17:56,770
have you ever listened to my advice once?

416
00:17:57,470 --> 00:17:58,270
Have you?

417
00:17:59,160 --> 00:18:01,090
Who does Zhang Xiaoman think he is?

418
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:02,730
Who do you think you are?

419
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:05,090
I'm telling you,

420
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:08,590
I own shares in this shop too.

421
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:10,570
I have a say in this.

422
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:13,030
Is that the reason

423
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:16,510
you want to send me to jail?

424
00:18:16,830 --> 00:18:17,640
Wang Tieda,

425
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:19,960
I'm helping you.

426
00:18:21,480 --> 00:18:23,440
With that little bit, you won't be inside for long.

427
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:24,000
Let me tell you,

428
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,110
I can make so much money.

429
00:18:26,270 --> 00:18:27,830
So much money.

430
00:18:27,830 --> 00:18:29,480
You're a damn jerk!

431
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:31,830
Stop it!

432
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:47,040
Zhigang, you were right.

433
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,930
We've just been playing house.

434
00:18:53,540 --> 00:18:54,780
We aren't gangsters.

435
00:18:57,130 --> 00:18:57,850
Go now.

436
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:01,710
Da.

437
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:02,880
Tell him to get lost!

438
00:19:17,940 --> 00:19:18,490
Fine.

439
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:22,680
Wang Tieda,

440
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:27,000
I'm done playing house with you.

441
00:19:52,920 --> 00:19:53,720
What's wrong?

442
00:19:54,590 --> 00:19:56,030
I heard you arguing.

443
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:57,730
Zhigang just rushed out.

444
00:19:57,730 --> 00:19:59,330
It's nothing. Stay out of it.

445
00:19:59,530 --> 00:20:01,930
Well, was that fake police report from him?

446
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:07,140
You brought Xiaodan here?

447
00:20:08,390 --> 00:20:09,020
Xiaodan.

448
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:10,570
Why are you here?

449
00:20:26,310 --> 00:20:28,670
Xiaodan, don't be mad.

450
00:20:29,110 --> 00:20:30,070
It was nothing.

451
00:20:30,070 --> 00:20:31,990
Just a misunderstanding between them.

452
00:20:31,990 --> 00:20:33,050
Xiaodan. Xiaodan.

453
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:37,030
I was wrong yesterday.

454
00:20:37,030 --> 00:20:38,400
I shouldn't have left you there.

455
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,270
But had to get involved

456
00:20:39,270 --> 00:20:40,790
in this.

457
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:43,970
Something bad would've happened today if I hadn't gone.

458
00:20:45,510 --> 00:20:47,570
There's something I want to tell you.

459
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:49,480
What is it?

460
00:20:51,430 --> 00:20:53,760
I've been thinking about this for a while.

461
00:20:55,110 --> 00:20:56,030
Well...

462
00:21:01,270 --> 00:21:03,530
I have an opportunity to study in France.

463
00:21:05,070 --> 00:21:06,400
And these next few days,

464
00:21:07,790 --> 00:21:09,850
I'm rushing to handle the paperwork,

465
00:21:10,440 --> 00:21:12,240
so I have to go back immediately.

466
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:13,800
You scared me.

467
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:15,440
That urgent?

468
00:21:22,950 --> 00:21:24,350
How long will you be gone?

469
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:27,880
Two years.

470
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:44,200
You really are flying higher and higher.

471
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:48,240
It's okay.

472
00:21:48,940 --> 00:21:49,900
Well...

473
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:52,360
It's just 2 years.

474
00:21:52,460 --> 00:21:53,060
Right?

475
00:21:53,830 --> 00:21:55,070
Okay. Two years...

476
00:21:57,110 --> 00:21:58,240
Two years go by fast.

477
00:21:58,300 --> 00:21:59,350
It'll be over in the blink of an eye.

478
00:21:59,350 --> 00:22:00,400
Yeah, it is fast.

479
00:22:00,550 --> 00:22:04,210
Hasn't it been 2 years since you graduated from technical school?

480
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:05,310
Yes.

481
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:09,510
So...

482
00:22:10,750 --> 00:22:11,920
have you booked your ticket?

483
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:13,400
When do you leave from Shanghai?

484
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,880
I'll go see you off.

485
00:22:19,950 --> 00:22:20,750
Is that it?

486
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:23,720
Just that?

487
00:22:27,990 --> 00:22:29,310
Take good care of yourself over there.

488
00:22:29,310 --> 00:22:31,120
And if anything happens, you can tell...

489
00:22:31,120 --> 00:22:32,780
Well, it's useless to tell me.

490
00:22:39,790 --> 00:22:40,790
When you come back,

491
00:22:40,790 --> 00:22:41,550
I'll go pick you up

492
00:22:41,550 --> 00:22:42,750
with Xia Lei.

493
00:22:42,790 --> 00:22:44,520
Why are you bringing up Xia Lei?

494
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:46,110
This is between the two of us!

495
00:22:46,110 --> 00:22:48,350
Why are you still bringing up Xia Lei?

496
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:49,750
What do you mean?

497
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:51,350
Our relationship now...

498
00:22:51,350 --> 00:22:53,640
Is the relationship between you and me

499
00:22:54,240 --> 00:22:55,640
the same as Xia Lei's relationship

500
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:56,880
with us?

501
00:22:56,960 --> 00:22:57,960
No, no. I...

502
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:59,620
No, I just said I'd see you off.

503
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:01,760
I didn't mean that.

504
00:23:05,440 --> 00:23:06,500
Then let me ask you.

505
00:23:06,830 --> 00:23:07,780
Let me ask you.

506
00:23:08,760 --> 00:23:10,890
What if I don't come back after 2 years?

507
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:15,630
What if I want to go to another country?

508
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:18,640
What if I go traveling around the world?

509
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:20,200
You just said you'd wait for me here

510
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,070
and pick me up.

511
00:23:21,070 --> 00:23:22,720
Then what?

512
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:27,200
Yeah, what about us?

513
00:23:27,550 --> 00:23:28,880
I'm asking you!

514
00:23:29,310 --> 00:23:31,110
You want to leave. What can we do?

515
00:23:31,350 --> 00:23:32,270
You travel the world,

516
00:23:32,270 --> 00:23:33,160
you go to France,

517
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:33,880
you go anywhere,

518
00:23:33,880 --> 00:23:34,550
you go to the moon—

519
00:23:34,550 --> 00:23:35,480
what can I do?

520
00:23:36,110 --> 00:23:37,840
I'm right here. I'm not moving.

521
00:23:38,520 --> 00:23:39,960
I don't want to hear this.

522
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:41,830
This isn't what I want to hear.

523
00:23:43,070 --> 00:23:44,830
I'm asking you what we're going to do.

524
00:23:44,830 --> 00:23:47,030
I just want you to tell me

525
00:23:47,030 --> 00:23:48,870
that we can be together.

526
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:51,600
No one said we can't be together.

527
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:53,680
I'm willing to wait here for you.

528
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:55,590
It's no problem.

529
00:23:55,590 --> 00:23:57,730
It's just 2 years. I'll wait for you to come back.

530
00:23:57,730 --> 00:23:58,960
When you're back, we'll be happy together.

531
00:23:58,960 --> 00:23:59,700
It's fine.

532
00:24:00,270 --> 00:24:01,880
But I'm afraid it might be more than 2 years.

533
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:03,790
I want you to show me where you stand,

534
00:24:03,790 --> 00:24:04,920
telling me clearly

535
00:24:04,920 --> 00:24:06,350
that you want to be with me forever.

536
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:07,080
Together...

537
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:08,880
That you want me to stay.

538
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:12,270
I want you to stay?

539
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:16,460
How do you think...

540
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:21,070
I could make you stay?

541
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:23,920
You're going to France.

542
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:25,350
France.

543
00:24:25,830 --> 00:24:28,090
How many people here have been to France?

544
00:24:28,920 --> 00:24:30,350
You have such a great opportunity. Why stay?

545
00:24:30,350 --> 00:24:31,610
What do I have to offer?

546
00:24:31,830 --> 00:24:33,560
This shabby little dance hall?

547
00:24:34,310 --> 00:24:36,110
Because I can sell clothes here?

548
00:24:36,360 --> 00:24:37,830
What right do I have to keep you?

549
00:24:37,830 --> 00:24:39,030
Why should I keep you?

550
00:24:39,750 --> 00:24:41,070
You have such a bright future.

551
00:24:41,070 --> 00:24:42,350
You have such a great opportunity.

552
00:24:42,350 --> 00:24:43,550
I'm stuck here with this trivial stuff every day.

553
00:24:43,550 --> 00:24:45,680
If I say, "stay here with me, Xiaodan,"

554
00:24:46,090 --> 00:24:47,370
wouldn't I be crazy?

555
00:24:49,590 --> 00:24:50,720
I can tell you this.

556
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:53,680
"Xiaodan, we will be together forever.

557
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:55,160
Stay here with me."

558
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:56,400
Will you stay?

559
00:24:57,570 --> 00:24:58,960
Is that what you want to hear?

560
00:24:58,960 --> 00:24:59,640
Don't go.

561
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:00,440
Just stay.

562
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:02,130
Can you stay?

563
00:25:02,350 --> 00:25:04,110
Haven't you already decided everything

564
00:25:04,110 --> 00:25:05,570
and just came to inform me?

565
00:25:08,590 --> 00:25:09,550
I can't leave here.

566
00:25:09,550 --> 00:25:10,880
I don't have the chance.

567
00:25:11,590 --> 00:25:12,750
Even though we grew up together,

568
00:25:12,750 --> 00:25:14,590
we're actually quite different.

569
00:25:14,590 --> 00:25:15,640
You want to go to Shanghai,

570
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:16,350
or France,

571
00:25:16,350 --> 00:25:17,240
you can just go.

572
00:25:17,460 --> 00:25:18,240
But how long would I have to save

573
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:20,160
to go to Shanghai?

574
00:25:21,590 --> 00:25:22,720
That is the reality.

575
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:27,030
I just want your attitude.

576
00:25:27,790 --> 00:25:29,920
I don't want us to lose to these things.

577
00:25:31,160 --> 00:25:32,640
I want you to tell me firmly.

578
00:25:32,640 --> 00:25:33,640
I want you—even if I go abroad—

579
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,070
to still tell me for sure

580
00:25:35,070 --> 00:25:37,350
that we'll never give up on each other.

581
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:40,250
My attitude is that no matter where you go,

582
00:25:40,510 --> 00:25:42,550
how far you go, or when you come back,

583
00:25:43,540 --> 00:25:44,600
I will wait for you.

584
00:25:46,270 --> 00:25:47,600
I'll be waiting for you.

585
00:25:52,880 --> 00:25:54,410
So you're letting me go now?

586
00:26:00,670 --> 00:26:01,870
I don't want you to go,

587
00:26:02,070 --> 00:26:04,070
but I have no reason to make you stay.

588
00:26:06,070 --> 00:26:08,920
It's such a wonderful place.

589
00:26:10,110 --> 00:26:11,510
And it's your dream.

590
00:26:11,580 --> 00:26:12,680
Haven't you always said since we were kids

591
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:14,680
that you wanted to travel the world?

592
00:26:15,030 --> 00:26:16,480
This dream is about to come true.

593
00:26:16,480 --> 00:26:18,720
How could I hold you back?

594
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:22,980
Just go without worry.

595
00:26:23,150 --> 00:26:23,640
It's okay.

596
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:26,550
I will achieve something here.

597
00:26:27,510 --> 00:26:28,270
I'm trying.

598
00:26:28,270 --> 00:26:31,640
I'm trying to find ways to make money.

599
00:26:32,150 --> 00:26:32,790
One day,

600
00:26:33,990 --> 00:26:35,640
I will close the distance between us.

601
00:26:35,640 --> 00:26:36,970
I will catch up with you.

602
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:40,750
That is the attitude I'm giving you:

603
00:26:40,750 --> 00:26:42,080
I will catch up with you.

604
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:32,350
Son.

605
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:35,200
Let me tell you,

606
00:27:35,590 --> 00:27:36,750
when people

607
00:27:36,960 --> 00:27:38,670
run into things,

608
00:27:39,590 --> 00:27:40,960
it's just like cars.

609
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:42,800
If it's dirty, we wash it.

610
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:44,400
If it's broken, we fix it.

611
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:47,550
If you just stand by and watch,

612
00:27:47,550 --> 00:27:49,080
will it get clean by itself?

613
00:27:49,550 --> 00:27:50,680
Will it fix itself?

614
00:27:51,350 --> 00:27:52,070
Right?

615
00:27:53,310 --> 00:27:55,910
Come on. I've wet that side. Put some foam on it.

616
00:28:00,310 --> 00:28:01,440
I...

617
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:04,110
pick up passengers all day long,

618
00:28:04,550 --> 00:28:06,150
meeting all kinds of people.

619
00:28:07,440 --> 00:28:08,960
Some people don't know the way,

620
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:10,960
but they know where they're going.

621
00:28:11,470 --> 00:28:12,640
So I take them there.

622
00:28:13,440 --> 00:28:15,100
I take shortcuts, no detours.

623
00:28:15,550 --> 00:28:16,750
But some passengers,

624
00:28:17,230 --> 00:28:18,880
they know exactly how to go.

625
00:28:18,910 --> 00:28:20,350
Then I follow their route.

626
00:28:20,350 --> 00:28:22,000
Even if there's roadwork,

627
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,720
traffic jams, or roadblocks,

628
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:25,440
I just compromise.

629
00:28:25,460 --> 00:28:26,790
I don't argue with them.

630
00:28:27,790 --> 00:28:28,720
And some people,

631
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:30,290
they don't know the way,

632
00:28:30,920 --> 00:28:31,590
and they haven't been there.

633
00:28:31,590 --> 00:28:32,590
The place they want to go,

634
00:28:32,590 --> 00:28:34,190
I haven't been there either.

635
00:28:34,310 --> 00:28:35,110
So what do I do?

636
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:36,510
Should I just not go?

637
00:28:36,510 --> 00:28:37,440
That won't work.

638
00:28:37,440 --> 00:28:38,970
I have to ask around as we go.

639
00:28:39,070 --> 00:28:40,710
I‘ll get there eventually.

640
00:28:41,160 --> 00:28:42,220
Do you understand?

641
00:28:43,170 --> 00:28:43,970
Yes.

642
00:28:46,660 --> 00:28:48,100
Really?

643
00:28:50,240 --> 00:28:51,110
I got it.

644
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:54,920
But if you walk by the river often enough,

645
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:56,350
your shoes are bound to get wet.

646
00:28:56,350 --> 00:28:57,830
Why be afraid of wet shoes?

647
00:28:57,850 --> 00:28:58,850
We're not afraid.

648
00:28:59,110 --> 00:29:01,110
We're not afraid of failure either.

649
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:02,280
As long as you're confident,

650
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:03,000
brave, and cautious,

651
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:04,330
you can always keep going

652
00:29:04,330 --> 00:29:05,330
and push forward.

653
00:29:06,150 --> 00:29:08,310
When you're tired, go home and rest for a couple of days.

654
00:29:08,310 --> 00:29:08,960
Once you've recovered,

655
00:29:08,960 --> 00:29:09,790
get back to it.

656
00:29:10,280 --> 00:29:12,480
At worst, go home and I'll cook for you.

657
00:29:14,030 --> 00:29:14,600
Okay.

658
00:29:34,590 --> 00:29:35,220
Hello?

659
00:29:36,030 --> 00:29:37,430
I know you're listening.

660
00:29:40,270 --> 00:29:42,830
Is our rental apartment still available?

661
00:29:44,510 --> 00:29:45,370
The lease is up.

662
00:29:46,480 --> 00:29:48,010
I'm on my way there now. Why?

663
00:29:50,980 --> 00:29:54,380
I was thinking of going back to continue our startup with you.

664
00:29:54,670 --> 00:29:55,590
Where are you?

665
00:29:56,240 --> 00:29:57,720
I... I'm in my hometown.

666
00:29:59,720 --> 00:30:02,570
How come you figured it out as soon as you went back home?

667
00:30:02,570 --> 00:30:03,970
Isn't that what you said?

668
00:30:04,210 --> 00:30:05,930
You can't teach a person with words,

669
00:30:05,930 --> 00:30:08,450
but experience teaches them instantly.

670
00:30:09,510 --> 00:30:11,040
Why? Did something happen?

671
00:30:11,550 --> 00:30:14,070
I... I tasted failure.

672
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:16,050
It really didn't feel good.

673
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:18,240
So you know it hurts, huh?

674
00:30:22,650 --> 00:30:23,650
Can we still do it?

675
00:30:24,680 --> 00:30:27,830
But you only have technical skills.

676
00:30:29,480 --> 00:30:31,000
You don't know much about financing.

677
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:33,270
What if what happened before happens again?

678
00:30:33,270 --> 00:30:34,470
Let me think about it.

679
00:30:35,430 --> 00:30:37,740
Are you still mad at me

680
00:30:38,030 --> 00:30:39,890
because of what happened before?

681
00:30:40,980 --> 00:30:42,070
I... I just felt

682
00:30:42,070 --> 00:30:44,670
that I wasn't suited for this industry before.

683
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:46,290
I've figured it out now.

684
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:49,340
To do something, you have to be your own boss.

685
00:30:50,180 --> 00:30:51,240
I apologize to you.

686
00:30:52,750 --> 00:30:54,000
I'm sorry.

687
00:30:54,260 --> 00:30:54,780
What?

688
00:30:55,750 --> 00:30:56,680
I'm sorry.

689
00:30:57,030 --> 00:30:58,760
Are... Are you messing with me?

690
00:30:58,940 --> 00:31:00,010
So what if I am?

691
00:31:01,110 --> 00:31:02,790
You made me feel so bad back then.

692
00:31:02,790 --> 00:31:04,030
Do you think I'm as childish as you,

693
00:31:04,030 --> 00:31:05,360
leaving just like that?

694
00:31:05,960 --> 00:31:07,270
Actually, I've already made up my mind.

695
00:31:07,270 --> 00:31:08,730
Even if you didn't call me,

696
00:31:08,790 --> 00:31:09,960
I would call you.

697
00:31:10,310 --> 00:31:11,750
Your tech alone isn't enough.

698
00:31:11,750 --> 00:31:12,970
You still need me.

699
00:31:13,110 --> 00:31:15,070
Together, we'll take off.

700
00:31:16,620 --> 00:31:17,750
Just now, the moment

701
00:31:17,750 --> 00:31:18,960
you said sorry to me,

702
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:20,600
I had a bold idea.

703
00:31:21,350 --> 00:31:22,610
If we're going to do it,

704
00:31:22,960 --> 00:31:23,920
we go big.

705
00:31:24,530 --> 00:31:25,330
Wait for me.

706
00:31:40,590 --> 00:31:41,670
You seem a bit down.

707
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:44,400
What's wrong? Is something bothering you?

708
00:31:45,720 --> 00:31:46,980
Did Xiaoman bully you?

709
00:31:46,990 --> 00:31:48,520
Tell me. I'll go beat him up.

710
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:50,720
No.

711
00:31:50,740 --> 00:31:51,870
Uncle Ding, well...

712
00:31:52,880 --> 00:31:53,720
It's nothing.

713
00:31:54,750 --> 00:31:56,480
It's just that coming to this night market

714
00:31:56,480 --> 00:31:58,080
reminds me of our childhood.

715
00:31:58,110 --> 00:31:58,870
I see.

716
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:01,000
You have to speak your mind before it's too late.

717
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,480
If you wait for too long, it won't be the same.

718
00:32:02,480 --> 00:32:03,960
Just like these grilled chicken frames.

719
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:05,550
Cook them too long and they get tough.

720
00:32:05,550 --> 00:32:07,680
Keep words in too long and they go sour.

721
00:32:28,730 --> 00:32:29,250
Hello?

722
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:33,760
Hello, Xiaoman?

723
00:32:37,270 --> 00:32:38,030
Xiaodan?

724
00:32:38,640 --> 00:32:39,770
I'm sorry, Xiaoman.

725
00:32:42,050 --> 00:32:44,180
I shouldn't have pushed you like that.

726
00:32:46,670 --> 00:32:48,280
When we went to Beijing,

727
00:32:49,070 --> 00:32:52,130
I never thought I'd make it to the hosting competition.

728
00:32:53,750 --> 00:32:55,680
It was all because you were with me,

729
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:00,350
making me feel safe.

730
00:33:02,920 --> 00:33:03,590
After that,

731
00:33:04,960 --> 00:33:07,350
I only applied to Tongzhou University.

732
00:33:09,830 --> 00:33:11,890
My dad thought I was just spiting him,

733
00:33:12,720 --> 00:33:13,960
but I wasn't.

734
00:33:15,740 --> 00:33:17,600
Because I felt like I held you back

735
00:33:18,310 --> 00:33:20,440
and made you miss out on sports school.

736
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:23,240
I just thought

737
00:33:25,780 --> 00:33:28,380
I'd finish high school properly for both of us.

738
00:33:29,180 --> 00:33:29,940
But...

739
00:33:31,590 --> 00:33:33,550
if I really become Magellan

740
00:33:33,790 --> 00:33:35,110
and go abroad—

741
00:33:36,590 --> 00:33:38,160
the thought of us being apart

742
00:33:38,160 --> 00:33:39,680
really made me panic.

743
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:43,920
I suddenly lost my courage.

744
00:33:46,070 --> 00:33:46,680
Xiaodan.

745
00:33:51,510 --> 00:33:52,310
I understand.

746
00:33:55,030 --> 00:33:56,400
I... I understand.

747
00:33:57,110 --> 00:33:58,970
It's true that in the past 2 years,

748
00:34:02,310 --> 00:34:04,440
I haven't really accomplished anything.

749
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:05,680
It's okay.

750
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:07,400
No matter where you go,

751
00:34:07,400 --> 00:34:09,730
no matter how far you go or how high you fly,

752
00:34:11,280 --> 00:34:12,480
I'll always be there.

753
00:34:12,550 --> 00:34:13,949
I'll always protect you.

754
00:34:14,320 --> 00:34:16,280
Just go forward bravely.

755
00:34:16,610 --> 00:34:18,270
I promise I'll catch up to you.

756
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:30,190
We're meeting the eldest grandson from our family's first branch,

757
00:34:30,190 --> 00:34:31,650
Fan He. You can call him He.

758
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:33,510
He's the head of Jiangnan Agricultural Machinery Factory.

759
00:34:33,510 --> 00:34:34,480
Be confident.

760
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:37,670
He.

761
00:34:38,440 --> 00:34:39,480
We... we brought...

762
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:40,590
some wine.

763
00:34:40,800 --> 00:34:41,630
Hey, beautiful.

764
00:34:41,630 --> 00:34:42,480
Please step outside for a moment.

765
00:34:42,480 --> 00:34:43,840
We have business to discuss.

766
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:44,670
Come back later.

767
00:34:44,670 --> 00:34:45,510
Thank you.

768
00:34:49,920 --> 00:34:51,760
He, long time no see.

769
00:34:52,320 --> 00:34:53,440
Sit down.

770
00:34:53,760 --> 00:34:54,510
Sit.

771
00:34:56,239 --> 00:34:58,370
He, this is the wine we brought for you.

772
00:34:59,430 --> 00:35:00,680
This is my partner,

773
00:35:00,710 --> 00:35:01,460
Xia Lei,

774
00:35:01,670 --> 00:35:03,870
a top student from Huigong University.

775
00:35:03,900 --> 00:35:05,110
Let me formally introduce you.

776
00:35:05,110 --> 00:35:07,840
This is He, whom I often mention,

777
00:35:07,840 --> 00:35:08,480
Fan He.

778
00:35:08,710 --> 00:35:11,660
He's also the head of Jiangnan Agricultural Machinery Factory.

779
00:35:11,660 --> 00:35:12,430
Hello, He.

780
00:35:13,510 --> 00:35:14,110
Sit, sit.

781
00:35:16,510 --> 00:35:17,320
Weijie,

782
00:35:17,510 --> 00:35:18,960
I think you're smart,

783
00:35:19,510 --> 00:35:20,510
so I always like to

784
00:35:20,590 --> 00:35:21,790
give you some advice.

785
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:22,710
Yes.

786
00:35:23,630 --> 00:35:25,360
What have you been up to lately?

787
00:35:25,400 --> 00:35:28,230
I heard you started a website.

788
00:35:28,880 --> 00:35:31,650
Yes, we started a small website together.

789
00:35:32,150 --> 00:35:32,840
And...

790
00:35:33,150 --> 00:35:35,110
Xia Lei is very good

791
00:35:35,110 --> 00:35:35,920
with the internet.

792
00:35:35,920 --> 00:35:37,920
We help our clients make connections.

793
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:39,670
We have quite a lot of orders.

794
00:35:40,110 --> 00:35:40,760
Mr. Fan.

795
00:35:41,340 --> 00:35:42,440
Zhou's factory is

796
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:44,190
a client of Weijie's company.

797
00:35:44,710 --> 00:35:46,190
The internet business...

798
00:35:46,830 --> 00:35:47,910
It looks new,

799
00:35:48,590 --> 00:35:50,390
but it's just the same old thing.

800
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:53,360
For business like yours,

801
00:35:53,800 --> 00:35:55,000
a business directory

802
00:35:55,400 --> 00:35:56,670
plus two experienced salespeople

803
00:35:56,670 --> 00:35:58,270
would be enough to handle it.

804
00:35:59,610 --> 00:36:02,070
The business directory has its limitations

805
00:36:02,410 --> 00:36:05,110
and takes a lot of time and manpower to compile.

806
00:36:05,630 --> 00:36:07,480
But the internet covers everything.

807
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:08,760
It's... it's global.

808
00:36:08,760 --> 00:36:09,510
Its openness

809
00:36:09,760 --> 00:36:11,070
allows us to quickly find

810
00:36:11,070 --> 00:36:13,760
the commercial resources we need online.

811
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:16,440
He, trust me.

812
00:36:17,440 --> 00:36:18,710
The internet will definitely have

813
00:36:18,710 --> 00:36:22,230
huge commercial potential in the future.

814
00:36:24,190 --> 00:36:25,000
Mr. Fan.

815
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:27,510
See that? A top student indeed.

816
00:36:28,110 --> 00:36:29,770
He explained it very clearly.

817
00:36:29,870 --> 00:36:30,910
So, He,

818
00:36:30,960 --> 00:36:33,550
our website has a great future,

819
00:36:33,820 --> 00:36:35,890
but it lacks a bit of financial prospect.

820
00:36:35,890 --> 00:36:36,440
Right.

821
00:36:36,470 --> 00:36:37,240
So...

822
00:36:40,450 --> 00:36:41,510
If you want to do it,

823
00:36:41,880 --> 00:36:42,880
the way you're doing it now,

824
00:36:42,880 --> 00:36:44,960
on a small scale,

825
00:36:45,360 --> 00:36:46,160
is pointless.

826
00:36:48,440 --> 00:36:49,900
If you want to work with me,

827
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:53,550
Jiangnan Agricultural Machinery Factory has to take a controlling stake.

828
00:36:53,550 --> 00:36:54,840
You mean...

829
00:36:57,000 --> 00:37:00,330
The Internet Enterprise Directory can't take every order.

830
00:37:00,500 --> 00:37:02,030
Cut those messy businesses

831
00:37:02,330 --> 00:37:06,530
and focus on connecting the upstream and downstream of the industry chain.

832
00:37:09,070 --> 00:37:10,060
We'll listen to you, He.

833
00:37:10,060 --> 00:37:10,580
Come on.

834
00:37:11,190 --> 00:37:12,520
Let's drink mine, okay?

835
00:37:13,840 --> 00:37:15,590
Let's toast to He.

836
00:37:15,960 --> 00:37:16,560
To He.

837
00:37:16,580 --> 00:37:17,040
Come on.

838
00:37:17,510 --> 00:37:19,920
May we work together to achieve great things

839
00:37:19,920 --> 00:37:20,800
and create brilliance!

840
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:22,190
Bravo! Cheers!

841
00:37:22,190 --> 00:37:22,590
Bottoms up.

842
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:28,370
♪ So many mountains I've climbed, rivers
I've crossed, trial after trial ♪

843
00:37:22,590 --> 00:37:23,320
Bottoms up.

844
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:29,960
I told you to put it sideways.

845
00:37:28,390 --> 00:37:33,610
♪ So many cliffs I've scaled, risky roads
I've walked, bend after bend ♪

846
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:31,020
Move it further in.

847
00:37:31,510 --> 00:37:32,750
I'm counting on you for the content.

848
00:37:32,750 --> 00:37:33,800
I haven't graduated yet.

849
00:37:33,800 --> 00:37:35,030
I haven't even finished my thesis.

850
00:37:34,080 --> 00:37:40,460
♪ Through disasters I've caused,
hardships and hunger I've suffered ♪

851
00:37:35,480 --> 00:37:36,030
Unreliable.

852
00:37:36,030 --> 00:37:36,920
That's exactly why

853
00:37:36,920 --> 00:37:38,030
I chose the company's location

854
00:37:38,030 --> 00:37:39,920
to be the closest to your school.

855
00:37:40,230 --> 00:37:41,230
By then, everyone sitting here

856
00:37:40,490 --> 00:37:44,720
♪ The heart of the people
crossing the bridge rages like wildfire ♪

857
00:37:41,230 --> 00:37:42,560
will be your employees.

858
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:44,230
When you walk in from there,

859
00:37:44,230 --> 00:37:46,150
they'll all say, "Hello, Mr. Xia."

860
00:37:46,150 --> 00:37:47,190
Just tell me, isn't it awesome?

861
00:37:46,500 --> 00:37:52,140
♪ I've walked through dark alleys, hit
against high walls, fallen into the pond ♪

862
00:37:48,150 --> 00:37:48,800
Awesome.

863
00:37:52,110 --> 00:37:52,880
Are you ready?

864
00:37:52,160 --> 00:37:58,700
♪ I've pursued my ideals, hated this body,
and been to the middle of nowhere ♪

865
00:37:56,110 --> 00:37:58,630
Since you've already done so much,

866
00:37:58,720 --> 00:38:03,950
♪ Gazing at the moon in a foreign land
in the gap of the city ♪

867
00:37:58,840 --> 00:38:00,190
the rest is up to me.

868
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:02,030
Alright!

869
00:38:02,760 --> 00:38:03,600
Let's get to work!

870
00:38:03,600 --> 00:38:04,720
[Xun Fei Tian Xia Network Technology Co., Ltd.]

871
00:38:04,120 --> 00:38:08,360
♪ Wishing only for the credit of one
who has crossed the bridge ♪

872
00:38:10,290 --> 00:38:12,940
♪ Look at the river flowing ♪

873
00:38:12,960 --> 00:38:16,350
♪ Where will the young man
on the bridge go? ♪

874
00:38:16,370 --> 00:38:19,160
♪ The vibrant spring sees flying birds
and thriving greenery ♪

875
00:38:19,190 --> 00:38:21,730
♪ But my heart remains the same ♪

876
00:38:22,270 --> 00:38:26,160
♪ Listen to the wuthering wind
in the fog ♪

877
00:38:26,180 --> 00:38:28,410
♪ The one crossing the bridge
has no fear of the road ahead ♪

878
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:29,150
Mr. Xia.

879
00:38:28,440 --> 00:38:29,740
♪ With the figure fading away ♪

880
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:32,260
♪ The reckless youth is gone from now on ♪

881
00:38:30,400 --> 00:38:31,550
Time to eat, Mr. Xia.

882
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:32,710
Just leave it there.

883
00:38:32,710 --> 00:38:33,920
I'll visit you another day.

884
00:38:33,920 --> 00:38:34,360
Mr. Fan.

885
00:38:34,360 --> 00:38:34,960
Okay.

886
00:38:36,150 --> 00:38:36,960
Bye.

887
00:38:37,960 --> 00:38:38,540
What's wrong?

888
00:38:38,540 --> 00:38:39,480
He didn't eat again.

889
00:38:39,480 --> 00:38:40,630
I just took out his lunch

890
00:38:40,630 --> 00:38:41,960
and sent in his dinner.

891
00:38:42,160 --> 00:38:43,510
I've reminded him several times.

892
00:38:43,510 --> 00:38:44,370
Have you eaten?

893
00:38:44,710 --> 00:38:45,640
Okay, it's fine.

894
00:38:45,700 --> 00:38:46,160
You can go now.

895
00:38:46,160 --> 00:38:46,760
It's cold.

896
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:47,550
It's fine.

897
00:38:51,280 --> 00:38:52,070
Come in.

898
00:38:54,830 --> 00:38:56,400
You haven't moved all day.

899
00:38:56,760 --> 00:38:59,890
At this rate, the company's business won't move either.

900
00:39:00,450 --> 00:39:01,500
Have something to eat. Come on.

901
00:39:01,500 --> 00:39:03,710
The network beta test is almost here.

902
00:39:04,410 --> 00:39:06,400
There are still a lot of issues.

903
00:39:06,700 --> 00:39:08,450
The tech department needs to keep on it.

904
00:39:08,450 --> 00:39:09,880
I need to make some changes too.

905
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:10,710
Can you handle it?

906
00:39:10,710 --> 00:39:12,360
I have to, whether I can or not.

907
00:39:12,360 --> 00:39:15,020
If you can handle it, a few minutes won't matter.

908
00:39:15,070 --> 00:39:16,130
Eat first. Come on.

909
00:39:19,510 --> 00:39:20,710
The food isn't bad.

910
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:28,360
How are things on your end?

911
00:39:28,630 --> 00:39:31,490
I visited some companies and individual merchants

912
00:39:31,710 --> 00:39:32,510
to tell them about

913
00:39:32,510 --> 00:39:34,030
our future plans for the network.

914
00:39:34,030 --> 00:39:35,320
I hope the collaboration will work out.

915
00:39:35,320 --> 00:39:37,120
I don't think it'll be a problem.

916
00:39:40,840 --> 00:39:42,240
Mom, why are you still up?

917
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:43,690
Sweetie, you're awake?

918
00:39:43,920 --> 00:39:45,150
Did I wake you?

919
00:39:45,620 --> 00:39:46,820
What are you writing?

920
00:39:47,490 --> 00:39:48,490
Just scribbling.

921
00:39:49,510 --> 00:39:50,360
Let me see.

922
00:39:54,960 --> 00:39:56,250
Braised Pork Ribs.

923
00:39:57,880 --> 00:39:59,030
Braised Fish.

924
00:39:59,320 --> 00:40:00,420
Recipes?

925
00:40:00,630 --> 00:40:01,480
Why are you writing these?

926
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:02,920
Don't you know how to cook them?

927
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:04,580
These are all your favorites.

928
00:40:05,510 --> 00:40:06,970
You're going abroad soon.

929
00:40:07,350 --> 00:40:09,630
That Western food, bread and such,

930
00:40:09,630 --> 00:40:10,960
has no nutrition at all.

931
00:40:11,150 --> 00:40:12,400
In case you ever crave

932
00:40:12,400 --> 00:40:13,630
a home-cooked meal,

933
00:40:14,110 --> 00:40:15,960
you can follow these to make it yourself.

934
00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:17,970
When I went to the East Chemical Plant back then,

935
00:40:17,970 --> 00:40:18,720
your grandmother

936
00:40:18,720 --> 00:40:20,780
wrote them down for me just like this.

937
00:40:23,920 --> 00:40:24,690
Mom, you...

938
00:40:24,990 --> 00:40:26,650
Doing this so late at night...

939
00:40:26,880 --> 00:40:27,960
You made me hungry.

940
00:40:29,860 --> 00:40:30,860
Silly girl.

941
00:40:30,920 --> 00:40:32,850
I want Braised Pork Ribs tomorrow.

942
00:40:33,190 --> 00:40:35,590
Okay. I'll make it tomorrow.

943
00:40:45,480 --> 00:40:46,480
I'm just thinking

944
00:40:47,760 --> 00:40:49,420
that we graduated so quickly.

945
00:40:49,770 --> 00:40:51,770
Four years of college flew by.

946
00:40:52,460 --> 00:40:55,190
Tell me about it. No more winter or summer breaks.

947
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:58,560
Think about what I told you.

948
00:41:00,150 --> 00:41:02,070
Our company is really short-handed.

949
00:41:02,070 --> 00:41:03,480
I could even make you a department manager.

950
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:05,410
I wouldn't go even if you made me VP.

951
00:41:06,880 --> 00:41:08,400
So you're definitely not going?

952
00:41:08,400 --> 00:41:10,800
To be honest, when I first started college,

953
00:41:11,150 --> 00:41:13,680
I thought since I came all the way to Shanghai,

954
00:41:13,920 --> 00:41:14,670
I would have to find a job here

955
00:41:14,670 --> 00:41:15,960
after graduation.

956
00:41:16,320 --> 00:41:18,810
But going home for the holidays these past few years,

957
00:41:18,810 --> 00:41:21,140
I saw the factory getting worse and worse.

958
00:41:21,250 --> 00:41:23,110
You know, kids of our generation—

959
00:41:23,220 --> 00:41:24,420
some went to college,

960
00:41:24,450 --> 00:41:25,450
some are working,

961
00:41:25,760 --> 00:41:27,190
but no one wants to go back.

962
00:41:27,190 --> 00:41:27,980
Yeah.

963
00:41:28,510 --> 00:41:31,230
Our factory seems to be in a similar situation.

964
00:41:31,760 --> 00:41:32,710
So I've decided.

965
00:41:32,710 --> 00:41:33,570
I'm going home.

966
00:41:33,800 --> 00:41:35,800
Come on. What are you going home for?

967
00:41:36,840 --> 00:41:38,990
Whatever I can do.

968
00:41:40,240 --> 00:41:42,100
Have you really made up your mind?

969
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:43,110
I have.

970
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:46,320
Since you've made up your mind,

971
00:41:46,320 --> 00:41:47,700
I won't force you to stay.

972
00:41:47,700 --> 00:41:50,700
I wish you and your factory getting better and better.

973
00:41:52,500 --> 00:41:54,150
How many times have I said this?

974
00:41:54,150 --> 00:41:55,800
Responsibilities must be clear.

975
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:57,110
If the test fails,

976
00:41:57,110 --> 00:41:58,550
someone has to take responsibility.

977
00:41:58,550 --> 00:41:59,670
If I have to solve

978
00:41:59,670 --> 00:42:00,960
every problem you encounter,

979
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:02,510
when can we start the testing?

980
00:42:02,510 --> 00:42:03,150
Mr. Xia,

981
00:42:03,300 --> 00:42:05,160
we know there are still a few bugs,

982
00:42:05,480 --> 00:42:07,480
but everyone has been working hard.

983
00:42:07,800 --> 00:42:09,600
I know everyone is working hard,

984
00:42:09,630 --> 00:42:10,480
working overtime every day,

985
00:42:10,480 --> 00:42:11,670
even on weekends.

986
00:42:11,670 --> 00:42:13,230
But if the division of labor isn't clear,

987
00:42:13,230 --> 00:42:14,440
it will cause unnecessary internal friction.

988
00:42:14,440 --> 00:42:16,860
Wouldn't that be getting half the result with twice the effort?

989
00:42:16,860 --> 00:42:18,450
Let's touch base later

990
00:42:18,750 --> 00:42:20,360
and go over the workflow again.

991
00:42:20,360 --> 00:42:22,320
Don't worry. We won't delay the internal testing.

992
00:42:22,320 --> 00:42:23,780
Alright. Get back to work.

993
00:42:24,240 --> 00:42:24,720
Here.

994
00:42:27,480 --> 00:42:28,710
What brings you here?

995
00:42:29,060 --> 00:42:30,230
You've been so busy.

996
00:42:30,230 --> 00:42:32,450
You haven't come over for dinner in weeks.

997
00:42:32,450 --> 00:42:34,360
My mom was worried you weren't eating well.

998
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:35,890
She really looks out for me.

999
00:42:36,920 --> 00:42:39,480
I saw you scolding people just now.

1000
00:42:39,880 --> 00:42:42,080
It's different now that you're Mr. Xia.

1001
00:42:42,150 --> 00:42:43,840
I was just too worked up.

1002
00:42:44,070 --> 00:42:45,630
I'm not usually like that.

1003
00:42:46,230 --> 00:42:48,890
Starting a business can really change a person.

1004
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:51,820
How are things going with France?

1005
00:42:51,860 --> 00:42:52,850
I got the acceptance letter.

1006
00:42:52,850 --> 00:42:54,850
I just need to finish the paperwork.

1007
00:42:57,400 --> 00:42:58,530
What about Xiaoman?

1008
00:42:58,920 --> 00:43:00,550
He said he'd go to France with me.
